<h3 data-path-to-node="28">The Design Rationale</h3>
<p>The resulting brandmark is a harmonious interplay of the sun and the moon, symbolizing transformation. The infinite cycle of day turning to night mirrors the "let it all go" experience at The Neuma. Turned horizontally, the moon shapes evoke ocean waves, serving as a metaphor for deep immersion. The central circle represents the sun, held protectively by the outer crescents to signify community and the "collective." The geometric sharpness of the overall form reflects the clinical precision and high quality of the resort.</p>
<h3 style="margin-top: 2.28571rem; color: #02192b; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Fira Sans', 'Droid Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: bold; letter-spacing: -0.54px; font-size: 1.42383em;"><figure class="post__image"><img loading="lazy"  style="color: #313339; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: inherit; font-weight: 400; outline: rgba(13, 139, 242, 0.55) solid 2.4px !important;" src="https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/explain.webp" alt="Mark explain" width="756" height="660" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/explain-xs.webp 300w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/explain-sm.webp 480w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/explain-md.webp 768w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/explain-lg.webp 1024w"></figure></h3>
<figure class="post__image post__image--wide align-left"><br>I tried many other designs on the computer but I think the moon and sun logo had the most potential. <br><br><img  style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: -0.54px; margin-left: -70.2px; margin-right: -70.2px; width: 842.4px; color: #313339; font-family: sans-serif; font-weight: 400; outline: rgba(13, 139, 242, 0.55) solid 2.4px !important;" src="https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/alldesigns.webp" alt="" width="1200" height="299" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/alldesigns-xs.webp 300w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/alldesigns-sm.webp 480w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/alldesigns-md.webp 768w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/alldesigns-lg.webp 1024w"></figure><figure class="post__image post__image--wide"><img loading="lazy"  style="margin-left: -70.2px; margin-right: -70.2px; width: 842.4px; outline: rgba(13, 139, 242, 0.55) solid 2.4px !important;" src="https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/moodboard-2.webp" alt="Moodboard Slide " width="1200" height="703" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/moodboard-2-xs.webp 300w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/moodboard-2-sm.webp 480w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/moodboard-2-md.webp 768w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/moodboard-2-lg.webp 1024w"></figure>
<h4><figure class="post__image post__image--wide"><img loading="lazy"  style="color: #313339; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: inherit; font-weight: 400; margin-left: -70.2px; margin-right: -70.2px; width: 835px; outline: rgba(13, 139, 242, 0.55) solid 2.4px !important;" src="https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/mood.webp" alt="Mood slide" width="1200" height="471" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/mood-xs.webp 300w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/mood-sm.webp 480w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/mood-md.webp 768w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/22/responsive/mood-lg.webp 1024w"></figure></h4>
<h3 data-path-to-node="30">The Hidden Visual (Negative Space)</h3>
<p data-path-to-node="31">A powerful secondary detail emerges within the negative space between the moon crescents and the central sun. The white space forms the silhouette of the <i data-path-to-node="31" data-index-in-node="154">Parvatasana</i> (the Seated Mountain Pose in Yoga), where the circle becomes the head and the crescents mimic hands extended upward. This posture promotes deep breathing and mental focus, aligning perfectly with the Neuma brand.</p>
